author: Vox
description:
The H-1B visa program isn’t perfect. While it does allow US companies to hire foreign workers who legitimately contribute rare intellectual skills, organizations often abuse the program as a way to acquire cheap labor. But, President Donald Trump’s $100,000 fee on new visa applications isn’t the be-all and end-all solution he thinks it is. Here’s why. #h1bvisa #immigration
